text: A discussion of the time complexity of the secondary structure calculations and a theoretical explanation for the contribution from pseudoknots is found in Text S2 (Section S2.3.1). Currently, the time complexity is approximately O(N 4.7 ) independent of the pseudoknot option. This is because the secondary structure methods have not been optimized. With optimization, the pseudoknot option can achieve a time complexity of approximately O(N 4 ).
